Yusuf Islam, formerly known as Cat Stevens, has made a surprise comeback with a new single featuring Ronan Keating.
Despite being deported from the US due to a name mix-up, he continues to pursue his music career.
Additionally, Nelson Mandela recently wore his prison number for an AIDS fundraising event, joined by music stars like Annie Lennox and Peter Gabriel.
Meanwhile, the band Chevelle, influenced by artists like Yusuf Islam, has found success with their album "Wonder What's Next."
Despite challenges, these artists continue to make an impact in the music industry.
